</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
A long-beaked variety in which the beak is at least half the length of the disc diameter and both the disc and the beak (or more rarely only the beak) are broadly winged (
<figureCitation box="[908,980,229,255]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,245,1605,1627]" captionTargetBox="[323,1275,713,1581]" captionTargetId="figure-303@7.[293,1293,685,1594]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Schematic drawing of Ranunculus achenes, side view: 1) R. marginatus var. trachycarpus from Turkey; 2) R. cornutus var. cornutus from Syria 3) R. cornutus var. scandicinus from Israel 4) R. cornutus var. leiocarpus from Azerbaijan. Author's illustration." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100600/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Distribution: Widespread in 
<collectingCountry box="[492,599,268,294]" name="Lebanon" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[612,678,268,294]" name="Syria" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Syria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[691,739,268,294]" name="Iraq" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Iraq</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[798,885,268,294]" name="Turkey" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Turkey</collectingCountry>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[930,996,268,294]" name="Israel" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Israel</collectingCountry>
it is known from a single herbarium specimen collected in the Sharon Plain near the town of Herzliya, 
<date box="[953,1122,306,332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1926-04-15">15 April 1926</date>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Eig, Zohary &amp; Feinbrun s.n.,</emphasis>
HUJ!). It has not been found there since and it is possibly extinct in 
<collectingCountry box="[1004,1073,345,371]" name="Israel" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Israel</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
